## Manual Verification & Walkthrough Guide

1. **Model Management**: Navigate to **Admin Panel -> System Settings** under **AI / LLM Settings**.
   - Input a new model (e.g., `mistralai/ministral-3-14b-reasoning`) and click **Add Model**.
   - The model is added as a chip. Click **Save All Settings**.
   - Verify that this model now instantly appears in the **Default LLM Model** dropdown options.
2. **Badge Connection**: Under **Allowed LLM Models**, notice the connection status dots. If LM Studio is online and a model is loaded, a pulsing green dot is visible; otherwise, a solid gray dot indicates it is configured but not currently loaded.
3. **Dynamic Filtering**: Navigate to **Admin Panel -> Analytics**. The **All Models** dropdown filter now dynamically loads the configured items from the database with premium formatted labels (e.g., `Gemma 2 9b (Google)`), and your dynamic dashboard charts will color-code them deterministically using high-contrast, professional styling.
